Okay, now where are these

00:38:00.690 --> 00:38:04.440
colonies?
Let me give you a little run

00:38:04.440 --> 00:38:06.325
down.
Before we get to that,

00:38:06.325 --> 00:38:09.019
I should say that the Greeks
have already,

00:38:09.019 --> 00:38:12.634
before this period of the
polis and the period of

00:38:12.634 --> 00:38:15.985
colonization which is connected
with the rise of the

00:38:15.985 --> 00:38:19.439
polis,
centuries before that the

00:38:19.439 --> 00:38:24.829
Greeks had already spread out
from their original settlements.

00:38:24.829 --> 00:38:29.969
Right after the collapse of the
Mycenaean world it was a period

00:38:29.969 --> 00:38:33.699
of tremendous confusion and
panic and fear,

00:38:33.699 --> 00:38:39.571
and so on, so that we know that
people fleeing from whoever

00:38:39.571 --> 00:38:45.746
destroyed the Mycenaean world
fled typically eastward into the

00:38:45.746 --> 00:38:49.483
island,
among the islands of the Aegean

00:38:49.483 --> 00:38:54.730
Sea and continuing on to the
coast of Asia Minor beyond them,

00:38:54.730 --> 00:39:00.436
so that by the tenth century
B.C., we see Greek cities lining

00:39:00.436 --> 00:39:04.050
the coast of Asia Minor on the
west,

00:39:04.050 --> 00:39:08.021
and even around on the bottom
and to some degree on the north,

00:39:08.021 --> 00:39:10.300
and on the islands in the
Aegean.

00:39:10.300 --> 00:39:15.380
So, there has been a
Greek--what's the word I want?

00:39:15.380 --> 00:39:18.568
There is an expansion of the
Greek world already by the tenth

00:39:18.568 --> 00:39:21.119
century, and these folks are now
settled down,

00:39:21.119 --> 00:39:25.773
so that some of these cities
are in fact among the most

00:39:25.773 --> 00:39:30.340
important cities sending out
colonies of their own.

00:39:30.340 --> 00:39:32.559
Of these,
the most famous,

00:39:32.559 --> 00:39:35.544
perhaps the most important,
was Miletus,

00:39:35.544 --> 00:39:40.059
an Ionian city located on the
west coast of Asia Minor,

00:39:40.059 --> 00:39:45.233
which sent many a colony into
different parts of the world,

00:39:45.233 --> 00:39:50.495
particularly up towards the
straits and the Bosporus and the

00:39:50.495 --> 00:39:54.549
Sea of Marmara.
I might point out that the way

00:39:54.549 --> 00:39:59.425
the Greeks did their immigration
into Asia Minor actually had a

00:39:59.425 --> 00:40:04.379
pattern so that you can go from
north to south and you will find

00:40:04.379 --> 00:40:07.469
some consistency.
Here's what I mean.

00:40:07.469 --> 00:40:14.195
The northern most settlements
on that coast spoke Greek with

00:40:14.195 --> 00:40:19.587
an Aeolian dialect;
the Aeolian dialect is the one

00:40:19.587 --> 00:40:25.881
that you see on the mainland in
places like Boeotia for instance

00:40:25.881 --> 00:40:31.466
Thebes and so on.
South of the Aeolian section of

00:40:31.466 --> 00:40:37.597
that was the region of Asia
Minor inhabited chiefly by

00:40:37.597 --> 00:40:41.145
Ionians,
the people on the mainland who

00:40:41.145 --> 00:40:44.179
are the main Ionians are the
Athenians.

00:40:44.179 --> 00:40:47.531
Finally, if you go to the most
southern part of the west coast

00:40:47.531 --> 00:40:50.607
of Asia Minor,
you come to the Dorian speaking

00:40:50.607 --> 00:40:52.946
Greeks and the whole
Peloponnesus,

00:40:52.946 --> 00:40:56.405
as you know,
was fundamentally a Dorian

00:40:56.405 --> 00:41:00.391
speaking place.
So that's the way the world

00:41:00.391 --> 00:41:05.973
looks when the polis is
invented and when colonization

00:41:05.973 --> 00:41:10.931
begins to become a big thing.
Now, let's take a look at

00:41:10.931 --> 00:41:14.826
the world of the Mediterranean
and see how Greek expansion

00:41:14.826 --> 00:41:18.679
worked.
Let's start with the Aegean Sea.

00:41:18.679 --> 00:41:23.834
Just almost all the islands in
that sea are inhabited by

00:41:23.834 --> 00:41:29.363
Greeks, mostly by the Greeks
that came in that first wave of

00:41:29.363 --> 00:41:34.539
immigrants earlier on,
not colonized during the eighth

00:41:34.539 --> 00:41:38.504
century and afterwards.
But if you go to the north

00:41:38.504 --> 00:41:42.407
shore of the Aegean Sea,
into the region that the Greeks

00:41:42.407 --> 00:41:46.235
called Thrace--sorry,
before I even get to Thrace,

00:41:46.235 --> 00:41:50.335
maybe even a little bit of
Thessaly which is off mostly

00:41:50.335 --> 00:41:54.346
west of the Aegean Sea,
a little bit but not Thrace

00:41:54.346 --> 00:41:58.570
chiefly, which is the northern
shore of the Aegean Sea,

00:41:58.570 --> 00:42:02.287
lots of Greek colonies there;
it's fundamentally part of

00:42:02.287 --> 00:42:04.524
Greece.
Yeah, this is not a bad time

00:42:04.524 --> 00:42:08.070
for me to remind you that in one
of Plato's dialogues,

00:42:08.070 --> 00:42:16.085
Socrates says the Greeks sit
like frogs around a pond and

00:42:16.085 --> 00:42:22.283
that pond is the Aegean Sea.
It's a helpful little story to

00:42:22.283 --> 00:42:25.963
remember, because we tend to
think of Greece because of its

00:42:25.963 --> 00:42:29.326
modern geography as that
peninsula of which there is a

00:42:29.326 --> 00:42:32.789
sub-peninsula at the bottom,
which is Peloponnesus.

00:42:32.789 --> 00:42:35.150
That was not the Greece of
antiquity.

00:42:35.150 --> 00:42:39.422
If you had to pick a central
focus of where the Greeks were,

00:42:39.422 --> 00:42:43.840
it would be in the Aegean Sea
so that's useful to remember.

00:42:43.840 --> 00:42:48.059
Then as you move east along
that coast, you come to the

00:42:48.059 --> 00:42:51.044
Gallipoli Peninsula,
all of which is now Turkey and

00:42:51.044 --> 00:42:53.630
for the rest of what I'm going
to be saying for awhile,

00:42:53.630 --> 00:42:56.627
it'll be Turkey as well,
but through the straits,

00:42:56.627 --> 00:42:58.750
the Dardanelles,
Sea of Marmara,

00:42:58.750 --> 00:43:04.320
Bosporus, Greek cities all over
on both sides.

00:43:04.320 --> 00:43:08.219
If you keep going east you hit
the Black Sea.

00:43:08.219 --> 00:43:12.652
If you move northwards along
the Black Sea and southwards as

00:43:12.652 --> 00:43:16.041
well, Greek cities,
not in the same number,

00:43:16.041 --> 00:43:20.608
they're fewer than they are in
the places I've mentioned so

00:43:20.608 --> 00:43:22.630
far,
but important ones.

00:43:22.630 --> 00:43:26.635
For instance,
when you get up to Crimea,

00:43:26.635 --> 00:43:31.666
the chief city we call,
Seastapole that comes from

00:43:31.666 --> 00:43:36.151
Greek words,
it means sebastos polis,

00:43:36.151 --> 00:43:40.000
the sacred city,
so named after Augustus by

00:43:40.000 --> 00:43:45.591
Greeks who lived there after the
Emperor Augustus had achieved

00:43:45.591 --> 00:43:49.094
power,
but it was always inhabited by

00:43:49.094 --> 00:43:50.936
Greeks.
Similarly,

00:43:50.936 --> 00:43:55.137
Odessa, the chief city of
Ukraine, apart from Kiev,

00:43:55.137 --> 00:44:00.179
was a Greek city and likewise
on the northern shore of Turkey

00:44:00.179 --> 00:44:03.539
there are Greek cities to be
found.

00:44:03.539 --> 00:44:07.510
One that leaps to mind is--how
do they pronounce it in Turkish?

00:44:07.510 --> 00:44:13.704
Is it Trebzond?
But it was Trapezos--what was

00:44:13.704 --> 00:44:18.809
it called in Greek?
Trapezos wasn't it?

00:44:18.809 --> 00:44:24.684
Anyway, the Black Sea is not a
Greek lake, but there are Greek

00:44:24.684 --> 00:44:28.730
cities that are spotted along
the coast.

00:44:28.730 --> 00:44:32.038
Now not on the east coast,
when you get to the Caucuses

00:44:32.038 --> 00:44:37.863
you are in barbarian territory.
So when the mythical mission of

00:44:37.863 --> 00:44:44.980
Jason and his Argonauts go
sailing out to that territory,

00:44:44.980 --> 00:44:49.394
he is out there in Tarzan
country, or as far as the Greeks

00:44:49.394 --> 00:44:52.648
were concerned,
it was just the wild out in

00:44:52.648 --> 00:44:57.760
that territory and remember he
marries and brings home a wife,

00:44:57.760 --> 00:45:01.804
Media, and she,
of course, is like no Greek

00:45:01.804 --> 00:45:06.000
woman who ever lived;
she is a witch.

00:45:06.000 --> 00:45:10.150
She can perform magic and she
can do monstrous things that you

00:45:10.150 --> 00:45:12.599
can't imagine a Greek woman
doing,

00:45:12.599 --> 00:45:16.345
at least the Greeks can't
imagine, so that's not Greek

00:45:16.345 --> 00:45:19.916
territory out there.
Well, let's get back out

00:45:19.916 --> 00:45:23.659
into the Aegean Sea and we just
crossed Asia Minor.

00:45:23.659 --> 00:45:26.390
Now, if you turn the bend at
the southern end of Asia Minor

00:45:26.390 --> 00:45:30.316
and begin moving east,
there are some Greek cities

00:45:30.316 --> 00:45:35.080
along in there,
but when you get to what is now

00:45:35.080 --> 00:45:38.414
Lebanon,
Syria, the coastal places

00:45:38.414 --> 00:45:42.626
there, Palestine,
there are no Greek cities there

00:45:42.626 --> 00:45:48.068
and that is because during the
period we're talking about those

00:45:48.068 --> 00:45:52.719
regions were occupied by
civilized powerful people who

00:45:52.719 --> 00:45:56.230
simply would not be pushed
aside,

00:45:56.230 --> 00:46:00.283
and nobody would even dream of
trying to take them on and

00:46:00.283 --> 00:46:04.408
building cities that would
challenge their control of that

00:46:04.408 --> 00:46:07.613
area.
So there are no Greek cities as

00:46:07.613 --> 00:46:10.989
you keep coming down and pass
Palestine.

00:46:10.989 --> 00:46:13.099
You reach Egypt,
and of course,

00:46:13.099 --> 00:46:17.037
Egypt is one of the great
empires of antiquity going back

00:46:17.037 --> 00:46:19.889
into,
perhaps, certainly into the

00:46:19.889 --> 00:46:23.342
fourth millennium,
possibly into the fifth,

00:46:23.342 --> 00:46:26.960
by no means as powerful as it
used to be,

00:46:26.960 --> 00:46:31.233
far from it.
It has been conquered by now by

00:46:31.233 --> 00:46:34.660
other peoples.
If you're talking about the

00:46:34.660 --> 00:46:40.030
year 750 or something like that
it's--I think it's in the hands,

00:46:40.030 --> 00:46:45.257
well, it is in the hands of the
Assyrians and it will ultimately

00:46:45.257 --> 00:46:48.409
fall into the hands of the
Persians.

00:46:48.409 --> 00:46:53.780
So that is not territory that
you can build colonies;

00:46:53.780 --> 00:46:55.880
you've got powerful empires to
deal with.

00:46:55.880 --> 00:46:58.714
There is one exception.
In the sixth century,

00:46:58.714 --> 00:47:02.088
I think it's around--imagine
around 550 or something like

00:47:02.088 --> 00:47:04.579
that,
the Greeks settle a single

00:47:04.579 --> 00:47:08.985
colony in the Delta of the Nile
of Egypt at a place called

00:47:08.985 --> 00:47:11.925
Naucratis,
and the root of that word is

00:47:11.925 --> 00:47:14.894
ship.
It is a completely different

00:47:14.894 --> 00:47:20.369
thing from the apoikia
that I've been talking about.

00:47:20.369 --> 00:47:25.077
It is a trading post and it's
there by permission of and under

00:47:25.077 --> 00:47:28.010
the protection of the King of
Egypt,

00:47:28.010 --> 00:47:31.427
and that's because he
wants--it's handy for him to

00:47:31.427 --> 00:47:35.472
have a merchant settlement of
Greeks for him to do business

00:47:35.472 --> 00:47:38.636
with.
So, that's a great exception to

00:47:38.636 --> 00:47:43.063
everything I've been saying.
Going west, would you believe,

00:47:43.063 --> 00:47:46.622
when you get into what is now
Libya, there was a very

00:47:46.622 --> 00:47:51.002
important Greek colony of Cyrene
and that whole region was called

00:47:51.002 --> 00:47:55.320
Cyrenaica and it was a Greek.
You can actually go,

00:47:55.320 --> 00:47:59.599
now that I realize that Libya
